title: Amber Robbins
text:
ajrobbins04@gmail.com
(702) 308-6129
Henderson, NV
LinkedIn Profile



Motivated computer science major with a burgeoning interest in data science. Proven team leader and collaborative team member known for strong interpersonal skills and meticulous attention to detail. Experienced in software design and web development, leading successful group projects and excelling in technical problem-solving. Seeking opportunities in a dynamic work environment to grow and contribute to a forward-thinking team, dedicated to continuous learning and excellence.




Programming Languages: Python, C++, JavaScript, HTML/CSS, SQL, Erlang (basic)
Web Development: Node.js, PHP
Advanced CSS Concepts: Flexbox, Grid, Animations, Responsive Design
Software Design: Object-Oriented Design, Design Patterns
Data Science Tools: Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-Learn, Plotly Express
Databases: MySQL, MongoDB
Version Control: Git, GitHub
Development Tools: VS Code, Xcode, Jupyter Notebook
Operating Systems: macOS, Linux (basic)





Leadership: Experience leading teams of 2-5 members in group projects
Collaboration: Strong interpersonal skills, effective team player
Communication: Clear and concise communicator, both written and verbal
Problem-Solving: Analytical thinker, adept at finding creative solutions
Detail-Oriented: Meticulous attention to detail, committed to quality work
Adaptability: Quick learner, capable of picking up new technical skills
Self-Motivated: Driven to succeed, dedicated to continuous learning and growth





Software Design: Designed and implemented software solutions using object-oriented principles and design patterns in various projects.
Full Stack Web Development: Developed full-stack web applications using Node.js and PHP, focusing on both front-end and back-end functionalities.
Object-Oriented Programming: Applied OOP concepts in multiple programming languages, including Python and C++, to build scalable and maintainable code.
Data Science: Utilized data science tools and libraries, such as Pandas and NumPy, to analyze and visualize data in various projects.
Functional Programming: Gained experience with functional programming paradigms and techniques through coursework and projects.




Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg, ID
* Bachelor of Science in Computer Science
* September 2020 - December 2025 (Expected Graduation Date)
* GPA: 3.9
Basic High School, Henderson, NV
* High School Diploma with Honors
* August 2010 - June 2014
* Valedictorian
